{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:proverbs.20",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 20,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 20 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.20.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:1",
      "text": "Wine is an intemperate thing, and strong drink full of violence: but every fool is entangled with them.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.20.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:2",
      "text": "The threat of a king differs not from the rage of a lion; and he that provokes him sins against his own soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.20.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:3",
      "text": "It is a glory to a man to turn aside from railing; but every fool is entangled with such matters.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.20.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:4",
      "text": "A sluggard when reproached is not ashamed: so also he who borrows corn in harvest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.20.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:5",
      "text": "Counsel in a man's heart is deep water; but a prudent man will draw it out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.20.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:6",
      "text": "A man is valuable, and a merciful man precious: but it is hard to find a faithful man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.20.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:7",
      "text": "He that walks blameless in justice, shall leave his children blessed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.20.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:8",
      "text": "Whenever a righteous king sits on the throne, no evil thing can stand before his presence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.20.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:9",
      "text": "Who will boast that he has a pure heart? or who will boldly say that he is pure from sins? 9a The lamp of him that reviles father or mother shall be put out, and his eyeballs shall see darkness. 9b A portion hastily gotten at first shall not be blessed in the end. 9c Say not, I will avenge myself on my enemy; but wait on the Lord, that he may help thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.20.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:10",
      "text": "A large and small weight, and divers measures, are even both of them unclean before the Lord; and so is he that makes them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.20.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:11",
      "text": "A youth when in company with a godly man, will be restrained in his devices, and then his way will be straight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.20.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:12",
      "text": "The ear hears, and the eye sees: even both of them are the Lord's work.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.20.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:13",
      "text": "Love not to speak ill, lest thou be cut off: open thine eyes, and be filled with bread.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.20.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:23",
      "text": "A double weight is an abomination to the Lord; and a deceitful balance is not good in his sight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.20.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:24",
      "text": "A man's goings are directed of the Lord: how then can a mortal understand his ways?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.20.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:25",
      "text": "It is a snare to a man hastily to consecrate some of his own property: for in that case repentance comes after vowing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.20.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:26",
      "text": "A wise king utterly crushes the ungodly, and will bring a wheel upon them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.20.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:27",
      "text": "The spirit of man is a light of the Lord, who searches the inmost parts of the belly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.20.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:28",
      "text": "Mercy and truth are a guard to a king, and will surround his throne with righteousness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.20.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:29",
      "text": "Wisdom is an ornament to young men; and grey hairs are the glory of old men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.20.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:30",
      "text": "Bruises and contusions befall bad men; and plagues shall come into the inward parts of their belly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
